# Security Module Rules

⚠️ ALL changes to this module require EXPLICIT USER APPROVAL before implementation.

- Encryption at rest via `pyrage` (age format)
- PII scrubbing via NER scan before disk writes
- Tool sandboxing via bubblewrap (no network, path allowlist)
- Tamper-evident append-only audit log
- Dead man's switch (auto-wipe if device leaves home network > 30 days)
- Vault for secrets with argon2 key derivation
- Zero-egress by default (LAN-only)
- Never commit secrets, `.env`, or encryption keys
